RESOLUTION NO. 21 By: Pugh
A Resolution recognizing the week of May 5 through
May 9, 2025, as Teacher Appreciation Week; and
honoring the invaluable contributions of teachers
across the State of Oklahoma.
our society, dedicating their lives to educating, inspiring, and
shaping the future of our children and communities; and
WHEREAS, the work of teachers extends far beyond the classroom,
as they serve not only as educators but also as mentors, role
models, and supporters for their students; and
WHEREAS, teachers consistently demonstrate creativity, patience,
resilience, and a deep commitment to student success, often going
above and beyond their responsibilities to ensure each child has the
opportunity to thrive; and
WHEREAS, the State of Oklahoma values the teaching profession
and acknowledges the need for ongoing investment in education and
support for those who choose this noble career path.
NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE 1ST SESSION
